# App Version Placement Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Display the current app version in the app/window title as `GoThru Photo Studio <version>` while keeping every native or HTML menu app label as `GoThru Photo Studio`.

**Architecture:** Keep product/menu label generation and window-title generation in the Tauri app-shell layer, using package metadata for the version. The Rust app shell sets the main window title during startup, macOS native menus use the product name only, and the Windows/Linux renderer menu removes its version suffix.

**Tech Stack:** Tauri v2, Rust, React 18, TypeScript, HeroUI, PowerShell, `cargo test`, `npm run typecheck`.

## Global Constraints

- Displayed app/window title format must be exactly `GoThru Photo Studio <version>`.
- Version must be read from app metadata/configuration, not hardcoded in UI or menu builder.
- Native menu/app-name label must display only `GoThru Photo Studio`.
- Menu items after the app-name label must remain unchanged: `File`, `Edit`, `View`, `Settings`, `Window`, `Help`.
- About/update flows may continue to show version information where they already do; this change only moves the version out of the menu label.
- Windows title bar/taskbar window title should show `GoThru Photo Studio <version>`; menu label should not include the version.
- macOS application menu name should remain `GoThru Photo Studio`; window title should show `GoThru Photo Studio <version>` where the OS displays document/window title text.
- Linux window title should show `GoThru Photo Studio <version>`; app/menu labels should not duplicate the version.
- No new localization keys are required for the product name or version string.
- Do not change update logic, bundle versioning, installer metadata, release signing, release version numbers, bundle identifier, or package metadata beyond the title display.
- Implementation must tolerate version changes without requiring code edits.

---

## File Structure

- Modify `src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs`: expose app-shell text helpers, remove the version suffix from the macOS native app menu label, and add unit tests for title/menu label formatting.
- Modify `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`: set the main Tauri window title during startup from `app.package_info().version`.
- Modify `src/renderer/components/layouts/Header/WindowsMenuBar.tsx`: remove the version suffix from the Windows/Linux HTML app menu label and remove the now-unused `config` import.
- No spec/docs changes are required beyond this implementation plan.

