### Task 1: Add App-Shell Title Helpers and Native Menu Label Test Coverage

**Files:**
- Modify: `src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs`

**Interfaces:**
- Produces: `pub fn app_menu_label() -> &'static str`
- Produces: `pub fn app_window_title(version: &str) -> String`
- Consumes: `APP_NAME: &str`, currently defined in `src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs`

- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing Rust unit tests**

Add this test module at the bottom of `src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs`:

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn app_menu_label_excludes_version() {
        assert_eq!(app_menu_label(), "GoThru Photo Studio");
        assert!(!app_menu_label().contains("1.1.1"));
    }

    #[test]
    fn app_window_title_includes_metadata_version() {
        assert_eq!(app_window_title("1.1.1"), "GoThru Photo Studio 1.1.1");
        assert_eq!(app_window_title("2.0.0-beta.1"), "GoThru Photo Studio 2.0.0-beta.1");
    }
}
```

- [ ] **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**

Run:

```powershell
cd D:\kantor\gothru-photo-studio-tauri\src-tauri
cargo test app_menu --lib
```

Expected: FAIL with errors that `app_menu_label` and `app_window_title` are not found.

- [ ] **Step 3: Add minimal helper functions**

In `src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs`, replace:

```rust
const APP_NAME: &str = "GoThru Photo Studio";
```

with:

```rust
const APP_NAME: &str = "GoThru Photo Studio";

pub fn app_menu_label() -> &'static str {
    APP_NAME
}

pub fn app_window_title(version: &str) -> String {
    format!("{APP_NAME} {version}")
}
```

- [ ] **Step 4: Remove the version from the native app menu label**

In `src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs`, inside `fn build_menu`, replace:

```rust
    let t = i18n::translator(app);
    let version = app.package_info().version.to_string();

    // About (on macOS, setting items live here instead of a separate Setting menu)
    let about = {
        let mut b = SubmenuBuilder::new(app, format!("{APP_NAME} {version}"))
            .item(&mi(app, "app:about", &format!("{} {APP_NAME}", t.t("t_about")), None)?);
```

with:

```rust
    let t = i18n::translator(app);

    // About (on macOS, setting items live here instead of a separate Setting menu)
    let about = {
        let mut b = SubmenuBuilder::new(app, app_menu_label())
            .item(&mi(app, "app:about", &format!("{} {APP_NAME}", t.t("t_about")), None)?);
```

- [ ] **Step 5: Run test to verify it passes**

Run:

```powershell
cd D:\kantor\gothru-photo-studio-tauri\src-tauri
cargo test app_menu --lib
```

Expected: PASS for `app_menu_label_excludes_version` and `app_window_title_includes_metadata_version`.

- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**

```powershell
cd D:\kantor\gothru-photo-studio-tauri
git add src-tauri/src/commands/app_menu.rs
git commit -m "test: cover app version placement labels"
```

