## Self-Review

**Spec coverage:** Task 1 removes the version from the macOS native menu label and tests the expected title/menu text. Task 2 sets the runtime app/window title from package metadata. Task 3 removes the version from the Windows/Linux HTML menu label. Task 4 verifies unchanged version metadata, menu ordering, About/update scope boundaries, and cross-OS QA evidence.

**Placeholder scan:** This plan contains no red-flag placeholder terms, no undefined function names, and no steps that ask the implementer to invent code without an exact snippet or command.

**Type consistency:** `app_menu_label() -> &'static str` and `app_window_title(version: &str) -> String` are introduced in Task 1 and consumed with the same signatures in Task 2.
